The paper discusses a sampling algorithm for high-dimensional distributions, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of MCMC techniques and rejection sampling suggests a focus on machine learning and optimization (cs.LG), while the mention of incremental refinements and exact optimization suggests a focus on algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The algorithm's potential applications in control systems (cs.SY) and neural networks (cs.NE) also make those sub-categories likely.
